  "text": "One group of algorithms, the best known of which is AQ [CITATION_1] , uses what they call decision rules as their family of classifiers, where they define the left-hand side of a decision rule as a disjunction of conjunctions. (Note the difference in terminology here: we define the left-hand side of a rule as just a conjunction of conditions, which is standard nomenclature for rule-based systems. Our rule packet (assuming that the contained rules have the same consequents) is the equivalent of their decision rule.) The AQ training algorithm uses heuristic search to find a logical expression which is as small as possible which classifies all the training examples correctly.",
