      "span_text": "One group of algorithms, the best known of which is AQ, uses what they call decision rules as their family of classifiers, where they define the left-hand side of a decision rule as a disjunction of conjunctions. (Note the difference in terminology here: we define the left-hand side of a rule as just a conjunction of conditions, which is standard nomenclature for rule-based systems."
